Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:07.840 --> 00:00:11.420
Transfagarasanul starts practicaly from the locality Arefu,

00:00:11.600 --> 00:00:17.780
 in the hydro Vidraru Massif which is located underground in fortress Cetatuia .

00:00:28.520 --> 00:00:43.820
The national road 7C starts from Pitesti and ends at the intersection with National Highway 1 (E86) in the locality Cartisoara.

00:01:04.060 --> 00:01:08.880
 Near the city Poenari the road climbs through the serpentines and viaducts, 

00:01:09.380 --> 00:01:19.020
going via three tunnels and reaches to the Vidraru dam, which is 307 meters long and 166 meters high;

00:01:19.020 --> 00:01:23.600
 the dam that connects Pleasa and Vidraru Mountains.

00:01:30.260 --> 00:01:42.220
Transfagarasan was achieved with effort and materials with the cost of many human lives in the years 1970-1974.

00:02:03.734 --> 00:02:11.134
For its construction was necessary to deploy several million tons of rock; 

00:02:11.140 --> 00:02:18.540
6520 tons of dynamite and tens of thousands of tons of concrete were used, 

00:02:18.920 --> 00:02:24.460
the road passes over 830 bridges and 27 viaducts.

00:02:34.640 --> 00:02:42.480
After the dam, the road continues on the left side of Lake Vidraru to its beginning.

00:03:10.920 --> 00:03:18.700
This section of road between the lake and waterfall, has a length of 13 km 

00:03:19.040 --> 00:03:24.080
and is considered the most difficult part of the Transfagarasan.

00:04:38.100 --> 00:04:46.400
Balea Tunnel is the longest tunnel in Romania, with a 4 m height and 6 m width. 

00:04:47.820 --> 00:04:53.120
Balea Tunnel can be crossed on foot on the sidewalk, which is  1 m wide,

00:04:53.600 --> 00:04:56.320
 the tunnel is lighted, but has a weak airflow.

00:05:06.134 --> 00:05:11.894
After Balea Tunnel, starts Transylvanian part of the Transfagarasan, 

00:05:12.340 --> 00:05:17.520
which passing through the natural reserve alpine and the Lake Balea.

00:05:42.540 --> 00:05:51.720
During the winter, between November, 1 till June, 30, in the part between km 104 from  Piscu Negru place, 

00:05:51.880 --> 00:06:00.200
which is on one side of the tunnel and  km 130 at Cabana Balea Waterfall on the other hand,

00:06:00.460 --> 00:06:04.180
Transfagarasan is closed for vehicle traffic; situated near of Balea Waterfal

